description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced Nurse to join the Dermatology Department at Christchurch Hospital. The post holder will work with the Dermatology Specialist Nurse and Consultant to provide a service for patients who are being treated with systemic agents, phototherapy and biologic agents. The successful candidate will manage a patient caseload under supervision and run nurse led clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic, highly motivated and enthusiastic individual to join our friendly team. The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate excellent communication skills, team working skills and dedicated to improving the patients experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is part time and is a fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust have now merged into the University Hospitals Dorset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: 26th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Malini Thomson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Title: Specialist Biologic Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: malini.thomson@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone Number: 0300 019 5476&lt;/p&gt;
